# Dependencies are installed fresh in the image (`pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`)
# before the source COPY. Baking the host's node_modules over them ships the
# wrong-arch binaries (host is often macOS, image is linux) and — critically —
# carries stale build caches (.vite / .vite-temp) that make the in-container
# build emit pre-edit code. Never copy node_modules from the host.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build output and bundler/transform caches. These MUST be regenerated in the
# container from current source. A stale host `dist/` or `.vite-temp/` baked in
# here is reused by the build and silently serves outdated compiled modules
# (this is what froze the homepage's getPublicRepos on the old query).
**/dist
**/.vite
**/.vite-temp
**/.turbo
*.tsbuildinfo

# Runtime data — provided by a mounted volume at /app/data in production.
# Baking the host DB/repos/LFS into the image shadows nothing (the volume wins)
# but bloats the image and confuses debugging.
data

# VCS / local tooling
.git
.gitignore
*.log
.DS_Store
.env*
coverage
.nyc_output
